{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T18:02:37.719Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Likelihood functions"},{"type":"text","text":" are the cornerstone of statistical inference that measure how plausible different parameter values are, given observed data—they tell us \"how likely the data is\" for each possible parameter value, and form the foundation of both Maximum Likelihood Estimation (finding the best parameters) and Bayes' Theorem (updating beliefs about parameters), making them essential for training generative models, estimating distributions, and understanding uncertainty in machine learning."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mathematical definition:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For observed data "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"D"},{"type":"text","text":" and unknown parameters "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"θ"},{"type":"text","text":", the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"likelihood function"},{"type":"text","text":" is:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"L(θ | D) = P(D | θ)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"L(θ | D)"},{"type":"text","text":" = likelihood of parameters θ given data D\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(D | θ)"},{"type":"text","text":" = probability of observing data D if parameters are θ\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Viewed as function of θ"},{"type":"text","text":" (not D)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key insight:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Likelihood = probability of data given parameters, but viewed as function of parameters\n\nP(D | θ) viewed as function of θ = L(θ | D)\n\nThe likelihood function is the probability density of getting the data that we actually observed, as a function of the value of θ [web:335]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Intuitive meaning:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Imagine you observed data D = [heads, heads, tails] from coin flips\n\nLikelihood asks: \"For which coin bias θ is this data most plausible?\"\n\nθ = 0.1 (rarely heads):     P(D|θ) is very small  → data unlikely\nθ = 0.5 (fair coin):        P(D|θ) is moderate   → data plausible\nθ = 0.7 (mostly heads):     P(D|θ) is largest    → data most likely\n\nThe likelihood function L(θ|D) tells you how plausible each θ is [web:335]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Likelihood vs Probability — Critical distinction"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The difference:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Concept"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it asks"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Variable"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Given θ, what's likely to happen?\""}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Function of data D"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Likelihood"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Given D, which θ is most plausible?\""}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Function of parameters θ"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Critical point"},{"type":"text","text":": Probability and likelihood are related but fundamentally different:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability"},{"type":"text","text":": P(data | θ) → asks about data, given fixed parameters\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Likelihood"},{"type":"text","text":": L(θ | data) → asks about parameters, given fixed data"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coin flip experiment:\n- Observed data: 2 heads, 1 tail\n\nProbability P(D|θ):\n  θ = 0.3: P(2H,1T) = 0.3² × 0.7 = 0.063\n  θ = 0.5: P(2H,1T) = 0.5² × 0.5 = 0.125\n  θ = 0.7: P(2H,1T) = 0.7² × 0.3 = 0.147\n\nLikelihood L(θ|D) = same values, but viewed as function of θ:\n  L(θ=0.3|D) = 0.063 (low plausibility)\n  L(θ=0.5|D) = 0.125 (moderate plausibility)\n  L(θ=0.7|D) = 0.147 (high plausibility)\n\nPeak at θ ≈ 0.7 (2/3 heads) ✓ [web:335]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Likelihood for multiple observations"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Product of likelihoods:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For independent observations "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"D = {x₁, x₂,..., xₙ}"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"L(θ | D) = P(x₁, x₂, ..., xₙ | θ)\n         = P(x₁ | θ) × P(x₂ | θ) × ... × P(xₙ | θ)\n         = Πᵢ₌₁ᴺ P(xᵢ | θ)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Log-likelihood (for computation):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"log L(θ | D) = log[Πᵢ₌₁ᴺ P(xᵢ | θ)]\n             = Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ log P(xᵢ | θ)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why log-likelihood?"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Logs are convenient because sums are easier to compute than products\n- Prevents numerical underflow (multiplying many small probabilities)\n- Maximizing log-likelihood = maximizing likelihood (same optimum)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[bernstein-network](https://bernstein-network.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/14_Lecture-14-Bayes-rule-and-maximum-likelihood.pdf)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Likelihood for coin flips"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data: D = [heads, heads, tails] (2 heads, 1 tail)\nParameter: θ = probability of heads\n\nP(x|θ) for single flip:\n  P(heads|θ) = θ\n  P(tails|θ) = 1 - θ"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Likelihood function:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"L(θ | D) = P(heads|θ) × P(heads|θ) × P(tails|θ)\n         = θ × θ × (1 - θ)\n         = θ²(1 - θ)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Log-likelihood:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"log L(θ | D) = log(θ²(1 - θ))\n             = 2 log(θ) + log(1 - θ)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finding maximum:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"To find θ that maximizes likelihood:\n  d/dθ [log L(θ|D)] = 0\n\n  d/dθ [2 log(θ) + log(1 - θ)] = 0\n  2/θ - 1/(1 - θ) = 0\n  2(1 - θ) = θ\n  2 - 2θ = θ\n  θ = 2/3\n\nMaximum Likelihood Estimate (MLE): θ = 2/3 ✓"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core idea:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Maximum Likelihood Estimation"},{"type":"text","text":" finds the parameter values that make the observed data most probable:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"θ_MLE = argmax L(θ | D)\n      = argmax log L(θ | D)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Algorithm:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Collect data: D = {x₁, x₂, ..., xₙ}\n\n2. Define model: P(x | θ)\n\n3. Write likelihood: L(θ | D) = Πᵢ₌₁ᴺ P(xᵢ | θ)\n\n4. Take log: log L(θ | D) = Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ log P(xᵢ | θ)\n\n5. Differentiate: d/dθ [log L(θ | D)]\n\n6. Set to zero and solve: d/dθ = 0\n\n7. θ_MLE = solution [web:334][web:335]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Gaussian MLE"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data: D = {x₁, x₂, ..., xₙ}\nModel: xᵢ ~ Normal(μ, σ²)\n\nLikelihood:\nL(μ, σ² | D) = Πᵢ₌₁ᴺ (1/√(2πσ²)) × exp(-(xᵢ - μ)²/(2σ²))\n\nLog-likelihood:\nlog L = -N/2 log(2π) - N/2 log(σ²) - Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ)²/(2σ²)\n\nMaximize w.r.t. μ:\n  d/dμ [log L] = 0\n  Σᵢ₝₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ) = 0\n  μ_MLE = Σᵢ₝₁ᴺ xᵢ / N = sample mean ✓\n\nMaximize w.r.t. σ²:\n  d/dσ² [log L] = 0\n  σ²_MLE = Σᵢ₝₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ_MLE)² / N = sample variance ✓"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Likelihood in Bayes' Theorem"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bayes' Theorem:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"P(θ | D) = P(D | θ) × P(θ) / P(D)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Which can be rewritten as:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"posterior = likelihood × prior / normalization"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Component breakdown:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Term"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Name"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Meaning"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(θ"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"posterior"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Updated belief about θ after seeing data"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(D"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"θ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"likelihood"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Probability of data given θ"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(θ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"prior"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Initial belief about θ before data"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(D)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"normalization"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant (total probability of data)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[towardsdatascience](https://towardsdatascience.com/understand-bayes-rule-likelihood-prior-and-posterior-34eae0f378c5/)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key relationship:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bayes' Theorem says:\nposterior probability density = prior probability density × likelihood function (times constant) [web:335]\n\nIf we take the prior and multiply it by the likelihood function, we get the posterior probability density [web:335]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual comparison:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bayesian approach:\n  Prior:    What we believe before data\n  Likelihood: What data tells us\n  Posterior: Updated belief (prior × likelihood) [web:335]\n\nMaximum Likelihood approach:\n  Only use likelihood!\n  Ignore prior\n  Find θ that maximizes likelihood [web:334]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Maximum Likelihood vs Bayesian Estimation"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Maximum Likelihood (MLE)"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bayesian Estimation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What it finds"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"θ that maximizes L(θ"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Full posterior P(θ"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prior used"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No (ignores prior)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes (incorporates prior)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Output"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single best θ value"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Distribution of θ values"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Uncertainty"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Not captured (point estimate)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fully captured (distribution)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Large data, no prior knowledge"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Small data, prior knowledge available"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": \"The ML estimate is the response-weighted average\" while Bayesian adds prior information."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Coin flip with Bayesian approach"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data: D = [heads, heads, tails] (2H, 1T)\nParameter: θ = probability of heads\n\nPrior: θ ~ Beta(α, β) (e.g., α=2, β=2 for uniform-ish prior)\n\nLikelihood: L(θ|D) = θ²(1-θ)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bayesian update:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Posterior: P(θ|D) = L(θ|D) × P(θ) / P(D)\n\nFor Beta prior + binomial likelihood:\n  Prior: Beta(α, β)\n  Posterior: Beta(α + heads, β + tails)\n  Posterior: Beta(2 + 2, 2 + 1) = Beta(4, 3)\n\nPosterior mean: (α + heads) / (α + β + N) = 4 / 7 ≈ 0.57\n\nMLE estimate: heads / N = 2 / 3 ≈ 0.67\n\nBayesian pulls estimate toward prior mean (0.5) ✓"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Log-likelihood in machine learning"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Connection to loss functions:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"In ML, we often minimize negative log-likelihood:\n\nLoss(θ) = -log L(θ | D) = -Σ log P(xᵢ | θ)\n\nFor classification:\n  -log P(y|x) = cross-entropy loss ✓\n\nFor regression (Gaussian):\n  -log P(y|x) = (y - ŷ)² = MSE loss ✓"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why cross-entropy = negative log-likelihood:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Classification:\n  P(y|x) = model's predicted probability for true class y\n  \nLoss = -log P(y|x)\n\nThis is exactly cross-entropy loss! [web:334]\n\nCross-entropy loss = negative log-likelihood of the correct class"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Likelihood formula"},{"type":"text","text":": L(θ|D) = P(D|θ) (probability of data given θ, viewed as function of θ)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Meaning"},{"type":"text","text":": How plausible each parameter value is, given observed data"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Likelihood vs Probability"},{"type":"text","text":": Probability = P(data|θ); Likelihood = L(θ|data)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multiple observations"},{"type":"text","text":": L(θ|D) = Πᵢₛ₁ᴺ P(xᵢ|θ)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Log-likelihood"},{"type":"text","text":": log L = Σ log P(xᵢ|θ) (easier to compute)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MLE"},{"type":"text","text":": θ"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"MLE = argmax L(θ|D) = argmax log L(θ|D)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coin MLE"},{"type":"text","text":": θ = heads/N (e.g., 2/3 for 2H, 1T)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gaussian MLE"},{"type":"text","text":": μ = sample mean, σ² = sample variance"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bayes' Theorem"},{"type":"text","text":": P(θ|D) = P(D|θ) × P(θ) / P(D) = likelihood × prior / normalization"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Posterior"},{"type":"text","text":": Updated belief = prior × likelihood"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MLE vs Bayesian"},{"type":"text","text":": MLE ignores prior, finds single best θ; Bayesian uses prior, finds distribution"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cross-entropy"},{"type":"text","text":": Negative log-likelihood of correct class"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MLE goal"},{"type":"text","text":": Find parameters that make observed data most probable"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bayesian goal"},{"type":"text","text":": Update beliefs about parameters using data and prior"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For Generative AI, likelihood functions are absolutely fundamental: Maximum Likelihood Estimation trains language models like GPT by maximizing the likelihood of next tokens (equivalent to minimizing cross-entropy loss), Bayesian methods estimate uncertainty in model parameters, generative models learn data distributions by maximizing likelihood of training samples, and variational inference uses likelihood to fit approximate distributions to complex posteriors—making likelihood the bridge between observed data and learned parameters; understanding likelihood is essential for mastering how neural networks learn from data and how generative models capture distributions."}]}]}}
